Argued June 21, TROY WAYNE WEDDLE, Appellant, v. CUPP, Respondent. (No. 75559) 497 P2d 1217 Ken C. Hadley, Deputy Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause for appellant. With him on the brief was Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem. Robert L. Misner, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osburn, Solicitor General, Salem.

affirmed June 21, 1972

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Langtry and Foley, Judges.
